    "description":  "when planning for the birth of a child, as families\u0026#160; time off during the first year following their child’s birth. policies on　Paternity Leave　and　Shared Parental Leave　to ensure that employees are fully aware of the options available to them and their family.　The　Nursery　also provides childcare at subsidised rates depending on eligibility and availability.This policy sets out all entitlements and associated processes that apply to the available maternity leave and pay options.Ordinary Maternity Leave (OML)The first 26 week period of maternity leave entitlement during which the employee will continue to receive all relevant terms and conditions of employment except salary and pension. If entitled to SMP, this will be paid for the full 26 week period.Maternity Allowance (MA)This is paid (up to 39 weeks) to employees who are not entitled to SMP but who meet the qualifying conditions for Maternity Allowance.Shared Parental Leave (SPL)An alternative or supplementary option to maternity leave, which allows a mother to reduce their maternity leave entitlement and share the remainder of their time off with their partner. Details are available in the University’s Shared Parental Leave Policy",
